ABSTRACT

This whitepaper presents the QUEENNE Plasma Engine (QPE) —a revolutionary propulsion system that integrates a governed cognitive intelligence stack directly into the plasma generation and control loop. By embedding the complete QUEENNE supercomputer architecture—including Triad AI ethical governance, Nuclear Intelligence (QNI), hybrid photonic-electronic computing, neuromorphic adaptive learning, and quantum-assisted optimization—the QPE transcends the fundamental limitations of conventional plasma thrusters. The system achieves unprecedented fuel efficiency (Isp up to 12,000 seconds), adaptive plasma instability suppression, intelligent erosion management, and autonomous mission optimization, all within an ethical governance framework. This paper details the system architecture, key technologies, performance characteristics, and implementation roadmap for a propulsion system capable of enabling humanity's next great leaps: Mars cargo transport, asteroid redirect missions, and interstellar precursor probes.

