6. PERFORMANCE ANALYSIS

6.1 Predicted Performance Envelope

Parameter Low‑Thrust Cruise High‑Thrust Maneuver Emergency
Power (MW) 1 8 10
Isp (s) 12,000 3,000 1,500
Thrust (N) 2 80 200
Efficiency (%) 85 65 50
Propellant H₂ Li Li

6.2 Lifetime Prediction

With intelligent erosion management, the QPE is projected to achieve:

· 50,000 hours at cruise power (Isp 12,000 s)
· 10,000 hours at high thrust (Isp 3,000 s)
· Total impulse: 1.2 × 10⁹ N·s (equivalent to 100 t of propellant at average Isp 6,000 s)

This is sufficient for a Mars round trip with 50 t payload, or a 15‑year interstellar precursor mission.

6.3 Comparison with Existing Technologies

Technology Isp (s) Thrust (N) Lifetime (h) Power (kW)
Chemical (RL10) 450 110,000 2 N/A
Hall thruster (BPT‑4000) 2,000 0.3 10,000 4.5
Ion thruster (NEXT) 4,000 0.2 50,000 7
VASIMR (conceptual) 5,000 5 10,000 200
QUEENNE Plasma Engine 12,000 100 50,000 10,000

The QPE offers an order‑of‑magnitude improvement in Isp at power levels that enable rapid interplanetary transit.

