7. MISSION APPLICATIONS

7.1 Mars Cargo Transport

Mission: Deliver 100 t of cargo to Mars surface in 180 days.

QPE Configuration: 10 MW, 85 t H₂ + 15 t Li

Profile:

· Earth departure: 30 days at 80 N (Isp 3,000 s, Li)
· Cruise: 120 days at 2 N (Isp 12,000 s, H₂)
· Mars capture: 30 days at 50 N (Isp 4,000 s, H₂/Li mix)

Advantage over chemical: 5× more payload for same launch mass, or 3× faster transit.

7.2 Asteroid Redirect Mission

Mission: Capture a 500 m asteroid and redirect to lunar orbit.

Challenges:

· Planetary protection (carbonaceous asteroid may contain organics)
· Precision navigation
· Long duration (3‑5 years)

QPE Role:

· Michael ensures non‑contamination (use H₂ only near asteroid)
· Gabriel plans optimal rendezvous and towing trajectory
· Rafael monitors asteroid stability during capture

7.3 Interstellar Precursor Probe

Mission: Reach 1,000 AU (Oort cloud) in 20 years.

QPE Configuration: 10 MW for first 5 years, then RTG power for 15 years.

Profile:

· Phase 1: Continuous thrust at Isp 12,000 s for 5 years → velocity 100 km/s
· Phase 2: Coast for 15 years → distance 1,000 AU
· Phase 3: Science observations with RTG power

Significance: First dedicated Oort cloud explorer, testing interstellar technologies.

7.4 Lunar Gateway Station‑Keeping

Mission: Maintain Gateway orbit for 15 years with minimal propellant.

QPE Advantage: Isp 12,000 s reduces station‑keeping propellant to <1 t over 15 years, freeing mass for science.

